Use custom dogpile cache key generator (#897)

* Use custom dogpile cache key generator

Dogpile cache cache only accepts byte strings as values for the default key generator. Passing non ascii characters results in `UnicodeEncodeError`.
By creating a custom key generator which converts unicode strings to byte strings, error is no longer thrown.
Fixes https://github.com/Diaoul/subliminal/issues/887 and also other `cache_on_arguments` calls where unicode strings are passed with non ascii characters.

* Fix custom dogpile cache key generator for python 3

Dogpile cache expects native string values.
In Python 2, this means byte string.
In Python 3, this means unicode string.

* Remove parentheses (due to auto completion)

* Fix key generator for non string values

* Rename custom key generator function

* Add test for custom dogpile cache key generator

* Fix test_cache for byte string value
